00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:58,250
他就能以医护兵的身份 留在军队里
provided he qualifies in all other areas in his training.

754
00:43:59,020 --> 00:44:02,370
或许我们可以帮助他 改变其想法
Perhaps we could help make believe in his idea.

755
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,970
没错 你让他只负责营房和厨房的杂事
Yeah, you restrict him to barracks in KP.

756
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:08,870
他只要跟你说起上帝 你就给他点颜色看看
If he throws God at you, you throw hell right at him.

757
00:44:09,010 --> 00:44:10,320
我要他走
I want him gone.

758
00:44:27,440 --> 00:44:29,130
道斯 你的床太乱了
Doss, your area is in disgrace.

759
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:30,880
简直就像个猪窝
It's a pig stock.

760
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,700
- 有什么好笑的吗 雷克 - 没有 中士
- Something funny, Ryker? - No, Sarge!

761
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:36,540
- 你脑子有毛病吗 - 没有 中士
- You got some shit on your mind? - No, Sarge!

762
00:44:37,870 --> 00:44:39,800
你们没有意识到的
What you men fail to recognize

763
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:43,670
团队中最弱者的能力 才真正决定团队的水平
is a unit is no better than its weakest member.

764
00:44:44,670 --> 00:44:46,420
为了帮助你们学习这个道理
Now, to help you learn that lesson,

765
00:44:46,720 --> 00:44:48,960
这个周末 所有人都不许外出
there will be no passes this weekend.

766
00:44:49,350 --> 00:44:51,130
全都滚到厨房去帮忙
You will all be on KP.

767
00:44:51,810 --> 00:44:55,200
现在 所有人全副武装 二十英里的负重越野
Right now everybody on full gear for 20-mile hike.

768
00:44:55,430 --> 00:44:56,430
快点
Let's go.

769
00:44:56,780 --> 00:44:57,780
出发
Let's go.

770
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:03,180
保持清醒
Get your heads right.

771
00:45:03,780 --> 00:45:06,050
不要自怨自艾
Don't start feeling sorry for yourself.

772
00:45:06,310 --> 00:45:09,130
看到你们自怨自艾的样子 我就觉得恶心
Makes me sick seeing you feel sorry for yourself.

773
00:45:09,330 --> 00:45:11,450
你们根本就不知道什么是累
You dogs don't know what tired is.

774
00:45:11,970 --> 00:45:14,170
我不停下 你们都别想休息
We gonna keep going till I drop.

775
00:45:16,410 --> 00:45:17,660
来吧 伙计们
Come on, guys.

776
00:45:22,570 --> 00:45:24,500
别打了 别打了
Hey, knock it off. Knock it off!

777
00:45:25,050 --> 00:45:26,450
我还要睡觉呢
Trying to sleep here.

778
00:45:29,750 --> 00:45:31,510
别碰我 别碰我
Get off me. Get off me.

779
00:45:39,170 --> 00:45:41,030
你他妈到底为什么还赖着不走呢
Why the hell are you still here?

780
00:45:51,380 --> 00:45:53,340
- 立正 - 稍息
- Ten-hut.- As you were.

781
00:46:01,350 --> 00:46:02,350
道斯呢
Where's Doss?

782
00:46:25,640 --> 00:46:27,100
这对任何人都没有好处
This isn't good for anybody.

783
00:46:27,380 --> 00:46:29,600
这确实不是我当初报名参军的原因
Sure ain't what I joined up for.

784
00:46:32,110 --> 00:46:33,790
这跟你参军的原因没关系
It's not about what you joined up for.

785
00:46:35,170 --> 00:46:37,200
而是关乎这里所有人的性命
It's about the lives of every men in here.

786
00:46:38,810 --> 00:46:40,210
还有你的性命 小子
And yours, son.

787
00:46:41,330 --> 00:46:42,600
是时候退出了
It's time you quit this.

788
00:46:44,240 --> 00:46:46,190
穿好衣服 我送你出去
Finish getting dress and I'll walk you down.

789
00:46:53,470 --> 00:46:54,470
没事的 道斯
It's okay, Doss.

790
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:57,990
没什么好羞耻的
There's no shame in this.

791
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,000
走吧
Let's go.

792
00:47:16,180 --> 00:47:18,490
我今天还要值班
I got an extra guard duty today,

793
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:21,440
早上还要去厨房帮忙 所以...
and I'm on KP this morning, so...

794
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:25,080
走不了
I can't.

795
00:47:31,430 --> 00:47:32,530
好吧 道斯
Alright, Doss.

796
00:47:35,270 --> 00:47:36,350
道斯二等兵
Private Doss,

797
00:47:36,930 --> 00:47:39,410
你能认出打你的人吗
can you identify the men that beat you?

798
00:47:46,230 --> 00:47:47,390
不 中士
No, Sarge.

799
00:47:48,050 --> 00:47:50,280
你是说 你不知道谁打了你吗
Are you saying that you don't know who attacked you?

800
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:53,710
我没说我被打了啊 中士
I never said I was attacked, Sarge.

801
00:47:54,810 --> 00:47:56,940
你到底在说什么呢 道斯
Well, what the hell are you saying, Doss?

802
00:47:57,720 --> 00:48:00,120
你睡觉睡得遍体鳞伤的吗
You bruised half your body sleeping?

803
00:48:02,010 --> 00:48:04,330
我睡相确实很差
I... I sleep pretty hard.

804
00:48:07,930 --> 00:48:08,730
好吧
Alright.

805
00:48:09,560 --> 00:48:11,060
如果这个周末 你们打算要享受艳福
If you plan on getting wet this weekend,

806
00:48:11,090 --> 00:48:13,390
- 要记得做安全措施噢  -下一个
- make sure you put on a hat. - Next!

807
00:48:13,430 --> 00:48:15,720
我可不想看你们带着一身骚味回来
I don't want anyone coming back pissing cream.

808
00:48:15,950 --> 00:48:18,100
难道你不想享受享受吗 中士
What, you don't want to none for your coffee, Sarge?

809
00:48:18,450 --> 00:48:20,710
那现在就来一发吧 史密提
How about a shot right now, Smitty?

810
00:48:21,020 --> 00:48:22,790
- 这是你的经验之谈吗 中士 - 下一个
- You speaking from experience, Sarge? - Next.

811
00:48:22,810 --> 00:48:25,020
你去问问你妈就知道了 胖球
You'd have to ask your mom about that, greaseball.

812
00:48:25,120 --> 00:48:26,550
敬礼
Move!

813
00:48:30,850 --> 00:48:31,850
稍息
At ease.

814
00:48:36,570 --> 00:48:37,780
道斯二等兵
Private Doss,

815
00:48:38,670 --> 00:48:40,710
恐怕我不能批准你外出
I'm afraid I can't authorize your pass.

816
00:48:40,740 --> 00:48:43,990
只有通过所有基础训练项目 才能享有假期
This is a furlough for men who had pass the basic training.

817
00:48:47,070 --> 00:48:49,650
恕我直言 长官 我已经通过了
Well, sir... respectfully, sir, I have.

818
00:48:50,990 --> 00:48:53,160
我三周前就开始申请这次外出了
I... I put in for this furlough three weeks ago.

819
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:55,670
今天下午 我就要结婚了
I'm getting married this afternoon.

820
00:48:55,690 --> 00:48:58,850
上面写着 你没有通过步枪测试
It says you're not rifle-qualified.

821
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:01,560
但我不需要佩枪 长官
Well, I'm not required to carry a rifle, sir.

822
00:49:01,590 --> 00:49:02,820
上校... 施特尔策上校 他...
Colonel... Colonel Stelzer he...

823
00:49:02,850 --> 00:49:05,460
施特尔策上校的规矩是说
Colonel Stelzer's determination was...

824
00:49:05,870 --> 00:49:08,520
"如果道斯想要留在军队 做医护兵
"Doss must be allowed to work as a combat medic,

825
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:13,090
他必须通过所有的训练测试"
provided he qualifies in all other areas of his training."

826
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:16,310
但你并没有通过步枪训练 二等兵
And you have not qualifiedon the rifle range, private.

827
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:18,120
非常清楚
Pretty clear.

828
00:49:21,340 --> 00:49:23,940
让我看看 你会不会拿枪
Show me you know how to handle a rifle,

829
00:49:24,190 --> 00:49:25,930
如果你会 我就批准你外出
and I'll sign your furlough.

830
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:28,320
- 坎农下士 - 长官
- Corporal Cannon. - Sir.

831
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:30,930
把你的佩枪递给道斯二等兵
Hand private Doss your firearm.

832
00:49:40,130 --> 00:49:41,270
我不会碰枪的 长官
I won't touch a rifle, sir.

833
00:49:41,300 --> 00:49:43,540
我没有在询问你的意见 二等兵
I'm not asking you, Private.

834
00:49:44,310 --> 00:49:47,150
这是指挥官给你下达的直接指令
That is a direct order from a company commander.

835
00:49:47,830 --> 00:49:49,830
看在上帝的份上 道斯
For God's sake, Doss,

836
00:49:51,010 --> 00:49:53,440
别胡闹了 退出吧
you stop this nonsense and quit.

837
00:49:54,420 --> 00:49:55,560
如果你拒绝
Refuse,

838
00:49:56,150 --> 00:49:59,100
那我就只能把你送上军事法庭了
and I will have no recourse but to court martial you,

839
00:49:59,510 --> 00:50:00,680
在整个战争期间
and you will spend

840
00:50:00,710 --> 00:50:03,600
你都将只能待在军事监狱里
the duration of the war in a military prison.

841
00:50:05,690 --> 00:50:06,980
我做不到 长官
I can't, sir.

842
00:50:19,390 --> 00:50:22,140
你还想等多久 多萝西
How much longer would you like to wait, Dorothy?

843
00:50:23,540 --> 00:50:25,540
我想 我们已经等得够久了
I think it's been long enough.

844
00:50:26,960 --> 00:50:28,270
很抱歉
I'm so very sorry.

845
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,450
有时候男人就会临阵退缩
Sometimes men just get cold feet.

846
00:50:33,490 --> 00:50:34,860
有些男人可能会吧
Some men might.

847
00:50:36,020 --> 00:50:37,600
但我的戴斯蒙德不会
Not my Desmond.

848
00:51:10,410 --> 00:51:12,700
你可能认为 我就是个混蛋
You probably think I'm a really son of a bitch

849
00:51:13,360 --> 00:51:15,930
只在乎规定 而不爱惜自己手下
who cares only about regulations and not his men.

850
00:51:19,440 --> 00:51:20,440
我可以看一下吗
May I?

851
00:51:27,310 --> 00:51:29,730
我和其他人一样 也对圣经深信不疑
I believe in this book as much as any men.

852
00:51:30,310 --> 00:51:31,550
也和其他人一样
And just like any man,

853
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:32,830
良心备受煎熬
I wrestled with my conscience,

854
00:51:32,850 --> 00:51:33,720
但当这世上你所珍视的一切
but what do you do

855
00:51:33,740 --> 00:51:36,650
都受到攻击时 你该怎么办
when everything you value in this world is under attacked?

856
00:51:37,880 --> 00:51:39,080
我不知道 长官
I don't know, sir.

857
00:51:40,870 --> 00:51:43,540
我不能回答如此深刻的问题
I ain't got answers to questions that big,

858
00:51:44,300 --> 00:51:47,500
但我也感觉到 我的价值观正受到冲击
but I also feel like my values are under attack,

859
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:49,520
我甚至都不知道为什么
and I don't know why.

860
00:51:49,870 --> 00:51:50,820
我可不在乎你那什么鬼原则
I don't give a rat-ass

861
00:51:50,850 --> 00:51:53,170
因为日本人也不会在乎
about your principles because the Japs don't.

862
00:51:53,810 --> 00:51:55,180
如果敌人袭击你
If one of them attacks you

863
00:51:55,210 --> 00:51:57,320
和其他受伤的士兵 你该怎么办
and some wounded soldier, what are you gonna do?

864
00:51:57,890 --> 00:51:59,490
用圣经打他吗
Hit him with your Bible?

865
00:52:00,230 --> 00:52:02,250
我愿意为我的队友 献出生命
I'm prepared to give my life for my men.

866
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:05,100
光靠牺牲自己的生命 并不能赢得战争
You don't win wars by giving up your life.

867
00:52:06,190 --> 00:52:06,950
听着
Look.

868
00:52:07,490 --> 00:52:08,210
我来这里
I'm only here because

869
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:10,520
是因为 我不想看到你被困在监狱里
I don't wanna see you rotting in a prison cell.

870
00:52:11,070 --> 00:52:12,070
认罪吧
Plead guilty,

871
00:52:12,220 --> 00:52:13,780
在法庭上 请求他们的宽恕
throw yourself at the mercy of the court.

872
00:52:13,810 --> 00:52:15,820
或许他们会让你安然无恙地回家
Maybe they'll let you go home and pray.

873
00:52:18,530 --> 00:52:21,100
让那些勇敢的人 去赢得这场战争吧
Let the brave men out there go and win this war.

874
00:52:30,010 --> 00:52:32,540
如果我说服不了你 或许她可以
If I can't convinceyou, maybe she can.

875
00:52:34,630 --> 00:52:36,630
他们不让我打电话给你
They wouldn't let me call you.

876
00:52:38,480 --> 00:52:40,410
我就知道这不是你的错
I knew it wasn't your making.

877
00:52:43,820 --> 00:52:45,360
他们对你干了什么
What've they done to you?

878
00:52:48,100 --> 00:52:49,320
没事 我没事
It's okay. I'm alright.

879
00:52:49,350 --> 00:52:51,970
我只是跟墙打了几个回合 然后输了而已
I just went a couple of rounds with the wall and lost.

880
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:55,450
他们说你很可能被送进监狱 戴斯蒙德
They're saying you could go to prison, Desmond.

881
00:52:56,460 --> 00:52:57,640
利文沃斯堡监狱
Leavenworth.

882
00:52:58,490 --> 00:53:00,160
肯定还有其他办法
There must be some other way.

883
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:02,150
我不知道还能怎么办
I don't know what that could be.

884
00:53:02,450 --> 00:53:03,780
除了碰枪这件事
I've done everything they asked me

885
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:04,760
他们说的我全照做了
except this one thing,

886
00:53:04,790 --> 00:53:05,970
就因为我不肯杀人
and I'm being treated like a criminal

887
00:53:05,990 --> 00:53:07,240
他们就如同对待犯人般对待我
just 'cause I won't kill.

888
00:53:07,270 --> 00:53:08,270
你尽力了
You tried.

889
00:53:08,830 --> 00:53:10,560
没人能否认这一点
Nobody can say you didn't.

890
00:53:11,560 --> 00:53:13,760
但你在监狱里 能救到谁呢
But who are you gonna save in prison?

891
00:53:16,020 --> 00:53:16,800
估计谁也救不了吧
Probably nobody.

892
00:53:16,820 --> 00:53:18,440
那你为什么 就不能拿起那该死的枪
Then why can't you just pick up the stupid gun

893
00:53:18,470 --> 00:53:19,590
随便装装样子呢
and wave it around.

894
00:53:19,860 --> 00:53:22,400
你不需要用它 只要做出让步就好了
You don't have to use it, just meet them halfway.

895
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:25,390
但我做不到
But I can't do that.

896
00:53:25,410 --> 00:53:26,690
你可以的 你只是太骄傲了
Yes, you can. It's just pride.

897
00:53:26,750 --> 00:53:27,630
骄傲又顽固
Pride and stuborness.

898
00:53:27,650 --> 00:53:30,000
不要混淆你的意志和主的意志
Don't confuse your will with the Lord's.

899
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,350
我很骄傲吗
Have I been prideful?

900
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:48,180
或许我确实很骄傲
Maybe I am prideful.

901
00:53:52,830 --> 00:53:54,720
但如果不坚持我自己的信仰
But I don't know how I'm going to live with myself

902
00:53:54,740 --> 00:53:57,030
我都不知道 该怎样生活下去
if I don't stay true to what I believe.

903
00:53:58,170 --> 00:54:00,690
更重要的是 该怎样和你一起生活
much less how you could live with me.

904
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:05,560
我永远不会成为 你眼中真正的男人
I'd never be the man that I want to be in your eyes.

905
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:14,080
我之所以爱你
I fell in love with you

906
00:54:14,910 --> 00:54:17,370
因为你跟其他人不一样
because you weren't like anyone else.

907
00:54:18,920 --> 00:54:20,590
而你也不曾改变自己
and you didn't try to be.

908
00:54:23,150 --> 00:54:27,610
永远不要觉得 你会让我失望
Do not think for one moment that you'll disappoint me.

909
00:54:30,480 --> 00:54:31,950
无论怎样
I will love you,

910
00:54:32,630 --> 00:54:34,140
我都爱你
no matter what.

911
00:54:46,460 --> 00:54:48,360
我不知道他要怎么办
I don't know what he's gonna do.

912
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:50,660
不管怎样 他都会输
He loses no matter what.

913
00:54:51,560 --> 00:54:52,660
他们想要他认罪
They want him to plead guilty

914
00:54:52,690 --> 00:54:54,940
但这样他就会被开除军籍...
but then he'll get dishonorable discharge...

915
00:54:55,510 --> 00:54:58,350
或者拒不认罪 那他肯定会进监狱的
Otherwise he fights them, he for sure goes to prison.

916
00:54:59,210 --> 00:55:00,590
不管怎样 他都会被人们称作懦夫
Either way, they'll call him a coward

917
00:55:00,610 --> 00:55:02,430
我不知道他怎么能那样活下去
and I don't see how he can live with that.

918
00:55:03,750 --> 00:55:05,930
谢谢 多萝西
Well, thank you, Dorothy.

919
00:55:06,930 --> 00:55:08,660
如果你有机会跟他说话
If you get to talk to him,

920
00:55:09,550 --> 00:55:10,590
告诉他 我们爱他
tell him that we love him

921
00:55:10,610 --> 00:55:11,880
我们为他祷告
and that  we're praying for him.

922
00:55:11,900 --> 00:55:13,090
为你们俩祈祷
We're praying for both of you.

923
00:55:13,960 --> 00:55:14,960
我会的
I will.

924
00:55:15,550 --> 00:55:16,550
再见
Bye-bye.

925
00:55:25,290 --> 00:55:26,890
你能不要烦我吗
Will you leave me alone?

926
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:29,130
你能走开吗
Will you just go?

927
00:55:29,270 --> 00:55:31,170
汤姆 你已经疯了 简直不可理喻...
Tom, you're out of your mind, you're delirious...

928
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,860
我当然是疯了
Of course I'm out of my mind.

929
00:55:32,890 --> 00:55:35,390
不然呢 我已经疯了
What do you think I am? I'm out of my mind.

930
00:55:35,660 --> 00:55:37,680
你给我滚出这间房 蠢女人
Will you leave this room? Stupid woman!

931
00:55:37,900 --> 00:55:39,320
天哪 把枪放下
God! Put it down!

932
00:55:39,350 --> 00:55:41,020
死女人 离我远点
Get away from me, woman.

933
00:55:58,910 --> 00:56:00,110
明白了 先生
I got that, sir.

934
00:56:12,020 --> 00:56:13,180
我有什么能帮您吗 先生
May I help you, sir?

935
00:56:13,270 --> 00:56:16,150
我想跟斯格罗夫准将说几句话
I wish to speak to Brigadier General Musgrove.

936
00:56:16,230 --> 00:56:17,370
没有预约 是不行的
Not without an appointment you can't.

937
00:56:17,390 --> 00:56:18,810
那是不可能的
That would be quite impossible.

938
00:56:25,710 --> 00:56:27,340
能请你转告他
If you would kindly tell him

939
00:56:27,360 --> 00:56:30,850
托马斯·道斯下士想跟他说几句话吗
Corporal Thomas Doss would appreciate a brief word.

940
00:56:31,540 --> 00:56:33,600
他在参加一个很重要的会议
He is in a very important meeting.

941
00:56:34,580 --> 00:56:37,220
在法国贝洛森林战役中 我曾与他并肩作战
I fought with him in France at Belleau Wood.

942
00:56:37,250 --> 00:56:38,880
当时 他是我的上尉
He was my Captain.

943
00:56:41,210 --> 00:56:44,680
求你了 女士 我有很重要的事
Please ma'am. It's... It's most vital.

944
00:56:48,230 --> 00:56:49,550
谢谢你 女士
Thank you, ma'am.

945
00:56:54,250 --> 00:56:56,870
外面有位叫做托马斯·道斯的人想要见您
There's a man out there, Thomas Doss, wants to see you.

946
00:56:56,890 --> 00:56:57,750
道斯
Doss?

947
00:57:02,430 --> 00:57:03,730
很快就能结束
Be over in a minute.

948
00:57:03,740 --> 00:57:05,170
你很快就能安全回家了
You'll be home safe and sound,

949
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:07,300
就像什么都没发生过一样
like nothing ever happened.

950
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:13,600
我爱你
I love you.

951
00:58:00,650 --> 00:58:02,780
本次听证会 被告为戴斯蒙德·道斯二等兵
This is a hearing into the matter of Private Desmond Doss.

952
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:04,390
其罪名为
The charge is disobeying

953
00:58:04,420 --> 00:58:06,890
不服从指挥官的多项指令
a series of direct orders from his commanding officer.

954
00:58:06,910 --> 00:58:08,530
被告方做何辩护
How says the defendant?

955
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:13,540
道斯二等兵 希望做无罪辩护
Private Doss wishes to enter a "not guilty" plea.

956
00:58:14,780 --> 00:58:16,680
是吗 二等兵 我本以为已经谈妥了
Is that so, Private? I thought this was agreed.

957
00:58:16,700 --> 00:58:19,360
你打算认罪 达成协议
You wanted to enter some sort of plea bargain.

958
00:58:21,120 --> 00:58:23,530
- 是的 长官 但我改变主意了 - 就这样吗
- Yes, sir. But I changed my mind.- Just like that?

959
00:58:23,540 --> 00:58:25,940
你想继续在军事法庭上辩护吗
You wish to proceed to a court-martial.

960
00:58:27,070 --> 00:58:28,070
是的 长官
Yes, sir.

961
00:58:28,590 --> 00:58:30,660
那后果自负 二等兵
Well, on your head, then. Private.

962
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:32,800
请继续
Proceed.

963
00:58:36,030 --> 00:58:36,890
法官大人
Your honor,

964
00:58:37,410 --> 00:58:38,710
道斯二等兵
Private Doss

965
00:58:38,850 --> 00:58:40,450
到处炫耀他的道德观
waves his morality at us,

966
00:58:40,480 --> 00:58:42,400
就像炫耀荣誉勋章
like it's some kind of badge of honor.

967
00:58:42,460 --> 00:58:43,990
通过违抗
He flaunts his contempt

968
00:58:44,020 --> 00:58:45,110
直属指挥官的一系列指令
by directly disobeying

969
00:58:45,110 --> 00:58:47,390
来显示自己的轻蔑之情
a series of direct orders from his commanding officer.

970
00:58:47,520 --> 00:58:49,020
与此同时 我们国家最出色的年轻人们
When the very best of our young men

971
00:58:49,040 --> 00:58:51,290
正在战场上 不惜生命 抗击...
are sacrificing their lives against...

972
00:58:54,270 --> 00:58:55,660
- 你还好吧 - 还好
- You okay? - Yes.

973
00:58:56,790 --> 00:58:59,130
- 还在审议吗 - 是的
- Are they still deliberating? - Yes, sir.

974
00:58:59,320 --> 00:59:01,350
好吧 你把这个拿进去
Okay, now you go take this in there.

975
00:59:01,370 --> 00:59:03,640
不行 非军事人员不得入内
I can't. It's strictly military personnel.

976
00:59:04,210 --> 00:59:05,680
那你要他们中一个拿进去吧
Well, then you get one of them to take it in.

977
00:59:05,710 --> 00:59:08,080
他们不会帮忙的 他们都恨不能把他埋了
They ain't out to help. They're fixing to burying him.

978
00:59:08,270 --> 00:59:09,610
军事法庭只需询问被告
There's only one question

979
00:59:09,640 --> 00:59:12,250
一个简单问题就可以了
that any military court need ask of the accused.

980
00:59:12,730 --> 00:59:16,440
你要否认 自己曾违抗塞恩斯顿上校的直接命令吗
Do you deny disobeying Colonel Sangston's direct orders?

981
00:59:19,160 --> 00:59:20,990
你否认吗 二等兵
Well, do you, Private?

982
00:59:26,830 --> 00:59:27,950
不 长官 我不否认
No, sir. I don't.

983
00:59:27,970 --> 00:59:29,700
那你到底在争论什么
Why are you contesting it, then?

984
00:59:29,830 --> 00:59:32,500
你既然拒绝触碰武器 那到底为什么
Why is it so important to you, given your refusal to even

985
00:59:32,530 --> 00:59:34,950
要加入战斗分队呢
touch a weapon to serve in a combat unit?

986
00:59:35,900 --> 00:59:38,260
因为在日本人袭击珍珠港后
Because when the Japanese attacked Pearl Harbor,

987
00:59:38,290 --> 00:59:39,890
我也感同身受
I took it personal.

988
00:59:41,260 --> 00:59:43,530
我认识的每个人 都热血沸腾地想参军
Everyone I knew was on fire to join up,

989
00:59:43,560 --> 00:59:44,730
其中也包括我
including me.

990
00:59:47,700 --> 00:59:49,680
在我的家乡 有两个人
There were two men in my hometown,

991
00:59:51,550 --> 00:59:52,820
因为体检不合格
declared 4-F unfit,

992
00:59:52,840 --> 00:59:55,220
没能入伍 而选择了自杀
they killed themselves 'cause they couldn't serve.

993
00:59:59,400 --> 01:00:01,140
之前 我在兵工厂工作
I had a job in a defense plant,

994
01:00:01,170 --> 01:00:03,710
本来可以申请延期服役 但那是不对的
and I could've taken a deferment, but that ain't right.

995
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:10,190
当其他人都在战场上 浴血奋战时
It isn't right that other men should fight and die,

996
01:00:11,020 --> 01:00:13,070
我却在家高枕无忧 这样是不对
that I would just be sitting at home safe.

997
01:00:13,140 --> 01:00:14,440
我要报效祖国
I need to serve.

998
01:00:16,450 --> 01:00:19,450
我有热情也有能力 成为一名医护兵
I got the energy and the passion to serve as a medic,

999
01:00:21,350 --> 01:00:23,610
与其他人并肩战斗 同甘共苦
right in the middle with the other guys, no less danger,

1000
01:00:23,640 --> 01:00:24,320
只是...
just...

1001
01:00:26,030 --> 01:00:27,570
当其他人都在夺取生命时
while everybody else is taking life,

1002
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:29,070
我将会拯救生命
I'm going to be saving it.

1003
01:00:32,590 --> 01:00:35,040
世界已经开始分崩离析
With the world so set on tearing itself apart,

1004
01:00:35,070 --> 01:00:36,890
而有人想要尽力 维持一点点原样
it doesn't seem like such a bad thing to me

1005
01:00:36,910 --> 01:00:39,270
在我看来 这似乎并不是坏事
to want to put a little bit of it back together.

1006
01:00:42,910 --> 01:00:44,400
- 抱歉 先生 任何人禁止入内 - 不
- Sorry, sir, nobody is allowed to... - No,

1007
01:00:44,430 --> 01:00:46,580
你不明白 我的儿子是被告
You don't understand. My son is the defendant.

1008
01:00:46,670 --> 01:00:47,570
我明白 先生
I understand, sir.

1009
01:00:47,590 --> 01:00:48,180
但任何人禁止入内
But nobody is allowed...

1010
01:00:48,210 --> 01:00:49,840
我有重要的消息
I have information, that's important.

1011
01:00:49,860 --> 01:00:50,630
先生 你不能...
Sir, you are not allowed...

1012
01:00:50,660 --> 01:00:52,760
虽然你表达的精神值得赞赏
While the sentiments expressed are laudable,

1013
01:00:52,790 --> 01:00:55,790
然而被控的罪行 却是无可争辩 所以...
the facts of the charge seem incontestable, so...

1014
01:00:56,870 --> 01:00:59,130
外面发生什么事了
What the hell is going on out there?

1015
01:00:59,740 --> 01:01:01,010
- 先生 - 让他进来吧
- Sir. - Let him go.

1016
01:01:12,310 --> 01:01:13,910
那是一战的制服
That's a Great War uniform.

1017
01:01:13,930 --> 01:01:15,160
是的 长官
It is, sir.

1018
01:01:15,660 --> 01:01:17,420
长官 我想让您看看这个
Sir, I need to show you this.

1019
01:01:17,450 --> 01:01:18,720
我没有冒犯的意思 先生
With respect, sir,

1020
01:01:18,780 --> 01:01:21,010
但您已经不再是军人了
you are no longer a member of the military.

1021
01:01:21,030 --> 01:01:23,390
您不能参加这次听证会 我很抱歉
You're unable to attend this hearing. I'm sorry.

1022
01:01:23,930 --> 01:01:26,110
现在军队真的是这样了吗 长官
Is that truly the way it works, sir?

1023
01:01:26,980 --> 01:01:28,360
你为国家而战
You fight for your country,

1024
01:01:28,390 --> 01:01:30,320
失去了许多宝贵的东西
you lose so much that were dear to you,

1025
01:01:30,350 --> 01:01:31,760
然后你却一文不值吗
and then you're done with?

1026
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:34,920
军装被遗忘 老兵被漠视
The uniform's forgotten. You have no voice?

1027
01:01:35,340 --> 01:01:36,530
您参加了里昂战役吗
You were at Lyons?

1028
01:01:36,660 --> 01:01:38,700
是的 长官 以及贝洛森林战役
I was, sir. And at Belleau Wood.

1029
01:01:38,880 --> 01:01:41,410
两次都被授予了勋章 我看到了 先生
Twice decorated. I see it, sir.

1030
01:01:42,340 --> 01:01:44,840
我想您是这位二等兵的父亲
I take it you're the Private's father.

1031
01:01:44,870 --> 01:01:46,880
没错 长官 我是托马斯·道斯
I am, sir. Thomas Doss.

1032
01:01:46,910 --> 01:01:48,470
那么作为一名退役军人
Then, as former military man,

1033
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:50,040
您应该知道这里的法律
you know there are laws here.

1034
01:01:50,070 --> 01:01:51,050
长官 我知道那些法律
Sir, I know the law.

1035
01:01:51,080 --> 01:01:53,400
我也知道 法律会维护我儿子应该有的权利
and I know my son is protected by those laws.

1036
01:01:53,420 --> 01:01:55,510
这些都是被宪法所保障的
They are framed in our constitution.

1037
01:01:55,920 --> 01:01:57,580
我相信这些法律 他也一样
And I believe in them, as he does.

1038
01:01:58,030 --> 01:02:00,500
正是为了捍卫我们的法律 我才会去报名参军
They are why I went and fought to protect them.

1039
01:02:01,580 --> 01:02:03,490
至少当初我奔赴战场时 我是这样想的
At least that's what I thought I was doing

1040
01:02:03,510 --> 01:02:04,810
因为 如果不是那样
because if it wasn't for that

1041
01:02:04,830 --> 01:02:07,870
那我就不知道我为何而战 长官
then I have no idea what the hell I was doing there, sir.

1042
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:11,630
谢谢您 道斯下士
Thank you, Corporal Doss.

1043
01:02:14,020 --> 01:02:15,550
把信交给我吧
Let me have the letter.

1044
01:02:23,320 --> 01:02:24,320
您必须离开
You must go.

1045
01:02:40,290 --> 01:02:41,570
"国会法案保护
"The defendant's rights as a

1046
01:02:41,600 --> 01:02:44,650
被告所拥有 出于信仰拒绝服兵役的权利"
conscientious objector are protected by an Act of Congress."

1047
01:02:44,680 --> 01:02:47,910
"并且不能强迫他放弃这些权利
"And he cannot be compelled to waive those rights.

1048
01:02:48,830 --> 01:02:50,090
包括本案中
That includes in this case

1049
01:02:50,120 --> 01:02:52,870
他拥有的违反军令拒绝拿起武器的权利"
his disobeying orders to bear arms."

1050
01:02:53,130 --> 01:02:55,020
签名 斯格罗夫准将
Signed, Bridgadier General Musgrove,

1051
01:02:55,050 --> 01:02:57,490
华盛顿特区 作战指挥部
War Services Commander, Washington, D.C.

1052
01:02:58,010 --> 01:02:58,780
上校
Colonel?

1053
01:03:03,350 --> 01:03:05,470
我撤回指控 长官
I withdraw the charges, sir.

1054
01:03:05,590 --> 01:03:07,450
那么案件审理结束
Then this case is dismissed.

1055
01:03:08,060 --> 01:03:10,800
道斯二等兵 你被允许 可以手无寸铁
Private Doss, you are free to run into the hell fire of

1056
01:03:10,830 --> 01:03:13,960
冲进硝烟弥漫的战场了
battle without a single weapon to protect yourself.

1057
01:03:15,190 --> 01:03:16,990
你将重拾责任
You may resume your duties

1058
01:03:17,240 --> 01:03:19,120
受训成为一名医护兵
and begin training as a combat medic.

1059
01:03:25,390 --> 01:03:26,790
- 他在哪儿 - 走了
- Where is he? - Gone.

1060
01:03:26,810 --> 01:03:28,520
他出来就直接离开了 我求过他留下来
Straight after. I begged him to stay.

1061
01:03:28,550 --> 01:03:30,610
- 我告诉过他 你肯定想见他 - 我明白
- I told him you'd want to see him. - No, I understand.

1062
01:03:31,840 --> 01:03:33,770
等你回家了 告诉他 我爱他
When you get home, you tell him I love him.

1063
01:03:33,810 --> 01:03:35,970
好的 好的
Okay. Okay.

1064
01:04:15,370 --> 01:04:17,810
你一定要回家 回我身边
You better come home to me.

1065
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:33,100
# 山姆大叔微微笑 平静似小孩 #
Uncle Sam is smiling. Peaceful as a child

1066
01:04:33,430 --> 01:04:34,860
# 但千万不要把他惹恼 #
But never get him rowdy.

1067
01:04:34,880 --> 01:04:36,190
别唱了 大明星
Cut it out, Hollywood.

1068
01:04:36,220 --> 01:04:36,810
闭嘴吧
Shut up.

1069
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:38,410
- 现在你想玩了吗 - 拜托 别唱了
- So now you wanna play? - C'mon pipe down.

1070
01:04:38,440 --> 01:04:39,960
- 闭嘴吧  伙计 - 闭嘴
- Shut up, man. - Shut up.

1071
01:04:39,990 --> 01:04:42,000
我发誓 大明星 我要毙了你
I swear to God, Hollywood, I'll shoot you.

1072
01:04:42,020 --> 01:04:42,820
用袜子堵上嘴 可以吗
Put a sock in it, will you?

1073
01:04:42,840 --> 01:04:44,630
等我们到了再高歌也不迟
Save the choir for when we get there.

1074
01:04:44,990 --> 01:04:46,320
真是扫兴
Killjoy is here.

1075
01:04:49,460 --> 01:04:50,350
都让开
Give 'em room.

1076
01:04:50,380 --> 01:04:52,950
- 让开 - 借过
- Clear! - Clear! Move aside.

1077
01:05:40,670 --> 01:05:41,670
九十六步兵团
The 96th...

1078
01:05:42,350 --> 01:05:43,320
就剩这么点儿人了
Or what's left of them.

1079
01:05:44,320 --> 01:05:46,350
我们就是要去轮换这些人
These are the guys we are replacing.

1080
01:06:17,560 --> 01:06:18,570
- 看起来没问题  - 安全
- Seems good to me. - Clear.

1081
01:06:18,600 --> 01:06:19,880
- 没问题 - 很好
- As gold. - Good.

1082
01:06:21,010 --> 01:06:22,240
一切安全 中士
All clear, Sarge!

1083
01:06:40,650 --> 01:06:41,650
格洛弗上尉
Captain Glover.

1084
01:06:43,660 --> 01:06:45,260
我是曼威尔中尉 来自九十六步兵团
Lieutenant Manville. 96th.

1085
01:06:45,870 --> 01:06:47,560
我们来接受您的指挥 长官
We've been assigned to you, sir.

1086
01:06:47,780 --> 01:06:48,780
好的
Okay.

1087
01:06:49,480 --> 01:06:51,030
给他们弄些吃的 快点
Let's get these men some chow. Come on.

1088
01:06:51,060 --> 01:06:51,550
是 长官
Yes, sir.

1089
01:06:51,580 --> 01:06:53,920
- 这位是豪威尔中士 - 很高兴见到你
- This is Sergeant Howell. - Good to meet you, sir.

1090
01:06:53,940 --> 01:06:55,540
- 请坐 - 哪位是道斯
- Sit down. - Who's Doss?

1091
01:06:55,610 --> 01:06:56,610
坐下吧
Sit down.

1092
01:06:56,930 --> 01:06:57,930
在那边
Over there.

1093
01:07:00,860 --> 01:07:01,860
你就是道斯
You Doss?

1094
01:07:04,390 --> 01:07:05,880
我是尔文·塞克特
Irv Schecter

1095
01:07:11,180 --> 01:07:13,560
你 我还有佩奇
You, and me and Page here

1096
01:07:13,940 --> 01:07:16,960
是这片区域仅剩的医护兵了 所以...
are about the only medics weg ot left in this area. So...

1097
01:07:17,320 --> 01:07:19,260
我想我们将要团结协作
I guess we're going to be working together.

1098
01:07:20,050 --> 01:07:21,560
你们刚刚从前线下来吗
You just come off the line?

1099
01:07:22,140 --> 01:07:23,140
那里怎么样
What's it like?

1100
01:07:25,610 --> 01:07:27,070
我问 那里怎么样
I said, what's it like?

1101
01:07:30,570 --> 01:07:31,770
钢锯岭吗
Hacksaw?

1102
01:07:33,620 --> 01:07:35,240
我们攀爬了六次
We climbed up six times.

1103
01:07:35,500 --> 01:07:37,540
六次 都被他们击退
Six times, they threw us off.

